question:
What is the output of the following C code?

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
        printf("%d ", i);
    }
    return 0;
}
```

How many times does the loop execute?

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    for (int i = 5; i > 0; i -= 2) {
        printf("%d ", i);
    }
    return 0;
}
```

What is wrong with this for loop?

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    for (int i = 0; i < 10; i--) {
        printf("%d ", i);
    }
    return 0;
}
```
